reviews.text: As an Alaskan Native I had fun here with my children. Seeing all the art work, and village houses were a great experience into the way of living as the ancestors did. This would be a great place for anyone to see....
if you are a tourist here, please come here to learn about the history of alaskans! it is really interesting and fun! They sometimes have food trucks outside as well.

was really cool to see.

in the third grade field trip, we had to watch a movie where this girl accidentally eats a fly and the fly turns into a baby in her stomach and the girl was pregnant, then they cut the movie off because the time was out.

it’s been a few years and i still do not know what the ending was.

Very educational, Heritage Pride is so strongly represented here. Loved it. Although  it's slow season for the museum, the center is still open for business. We did however get a personal tour by one of the employee Wilson.  Very nice and informative

A MUST EXPERIENCE This center offers a variety of indigenous experiences... exhibits, videos, interactive displays, food, live performances, walking tours representing the villages, culture and home life of Alaska's first people. This voyage of discovery deserves a full day or a minimum half day.

I always love the tastefully constructed Anchorage Museum. The displays stoke a passion inside of me for Alaskan history and Art. Currently they have beanbag chairs in the sun room that provides for relaxation and reflection. Great spot to take a lunch break!

I really enjoyed this museum. I found the exhibits very balanced in terms of presentation. There is a beautiful gallery up top showcasing young indigenous artists, there is an extensive gallery about the history of Alaska, and the art collection is extensive. A beautiful building and wonderful exhibits.

This is a mid-size museum offering a look at traditional native Alaskan culture, and focusing on how that culture is blending with modern western culture. The museum recently was damaged by an earthquake, but most of it is open except the Smithsonian exhibit. It would be easy to spend a whole day here, though you can get a pretty good look in 2-3 hours. Also, be sure to check out the Planetarium show on the Aurora Borealis. 

Don’t bother with Muse (the restaurant) — take a walk to a local restaurant for lunch.

This museum is worth visiting whether you are from out of town or have lived in Alaska your whole life. Both parties will find stuff to appreciate here. All ages will love it. There is a robust kids activity center. My three year old daughter got to touch a lizard. I got to see some great art and learned more about the state I live in.
It's a quick visit, great way to understand Alaska culture.

Well designed, small museum. Every inch of the place is covered in interesting artifacts. The staff were very helpful, with lots of interesting things to say about all of the things on display. Can’t wait to go again to see the things I missed!
The awesome thing about it was it had the Hudson hornet highway patrol
I enjoyed it but it might just be because I'm a retired NYPD cop

It's a small little place, but if you have an hour or so on your hands I would definitely recommend going by. It's a very nice set up with some very cool information (if you're an Alaskan Native or Tourist) and the staff are very friendly.

Everything there on the history of the Alaska State Troopers. A current story book hard bound sold for $50. I thought a ridiculous price. I bought the  $20 paperback which I read and when finished I donated. Too many stories by the same people.
It's there, but you could hardly call it a museum. It does have a few nice pieces. I think exhibit is a better term for it.
I love this place. The man was super friendly and helpful and a wonderful host.

There are a number of beautiful native art pieces at this museum. If you enjoy a great Sydney Laurence painting, this the the place to be. The museum is free to the public and the main branch also has a number of Sydney Laurence paintings to view for free. The current curator, Tom Bennett, is always a pleasure to speak with and a wealth of knowledge.
I've been going to this bank for over a year and never noticed this museum until today. it's very little, but they have some really interesting real artifacts. it's free which is always nice.
Good place to study some history, but some of the artifacts are aimed at promoting Wells Fargo...
Lovely family owned business. Has huge portions and affordable prices. Mainly diner/American/Homestyle food. Quality and freshness of food is great! I would recommend to anyone :)
Good diner food but not fancy. Fast service and home cooked items like giant cinnamon rolls. My husband really liked the roast turkey dinner.

Had brunch with the family. Second meal here. Not bad food at all. The service was fast and friendly. We were very happy overall great tasting bacon! The pancakes were stellar. Really good flavor, light and fluffy. Chicken fried steak was good. I wish we had gotten a cinnamon roll. Was the size of a dinner plate!!
Quiet family friendly environment.  Quick service. Love the waitress. Where you go for home cooked style.

Amazing diner!! We went before work one day and it was lovely. It's cute and cozy with big servings and awesome service! They are seriously the sweetest people there. We came in uniform, which I try to avoid but couldn't that day. We we re thanks for our service by patrons and staff. Not that I ever expect that because I don't. It was just a very nice thing to have happened. The entire experience was so stereotypical TV show friendly diner. It was awesome! We'll be back!

Did I mention I got the veggie omelet and my veggies we're actually cooked AND crispy?!?

We ordered the Saimin which did not have much taste and did not seem to be fresh. 
The seared poke was good the rice with it was bit dry tough. The staff is very friendly and welcoming. It seems to be a laid back and family friendly place.
Very good meats.  Every member of my family had a different favorite.  Mac salad was so good, not sure why anyone would go for the rice instead.  Got a good spam musubi with the meal too.
Good food and huge portion sizes.  Staff was very friendly.  My favorite was the teri chicken, but really everything was pretty great.

Always a great experience. Its one place that we can bring our family and all of our picky little kids will clear their plates. The employees are always making you feel like you're at home there and prices are good.

Got the barbecue chicken and teriyaki beef. It was way over cooked like pieces of rubber it seemed  like it was old as well. Food was inedible. I wonder how these 5 star reviews they have are legitimate.

My husband and I have been living in Anchorage for a few months now and had never been to this diner.  You walk in an immediately get the feel of the 1940s and 50’s vibe. The music the malt shake bar, the wonderful service from staff. The cook from the kitchen always had a smile on his face. The food was wonderful, I had the chili burger and my husband had the Route 66 burger! Highly recommend.

So my wife and I had never been to this diner.  You walk in an immediately get the old timey diner theme. The malt shake bar, the wonderful service from staff was great! The food was wonderful. I had the 66 burger, and I would recommend getting that if you like a good burger!

The staff is always friendly, the portions are filling and they've got tons of booths.  Stopped by and found out the restaurant had changed hands.  Not a bad thing at all.  Still super friendly, our server Allison was so happy and on the ball.  Food arrived very quickly and was very tasty.

I can't believe I passed this diner so many times without ever going in there. The corned beef is amazing! It's REAL shredded corned beef! The food quality is way above what I expect from any diner and the prices are excellent here as well! The menu is far better than I expected as well. Inside is very clean and very nice! This is my new favourite place! You won't regret trying this place out.

Great food and service. 
Sat down and within 20 minutes we had our food at the table. 
Lovely retro feels and great malt and shake choices.
Fast service,  tasteful.  Staff is effective though quiet. Need to keep the dining room up. Not a bad lunch. A step up from Taco bell.

I don't think Burrito King can do wrong! They are awesome, the food is great, and the guy at the front remembered my order from last time. I find it impressive when shops remember your name and tastes. Keep it up!
Love their fried ice cream. Their chips and dip could be a little cheaper for the quality of the item. But over all it's amazing food and its filling for sure!

Really enjoy the breakfast they have here.. I ordered the Mexican Omelet and it truly was great.. it is not on the menu anymore but was in the past.. They will still make it for you if you request the Mexican Omelet with Rice and Beans...
Food tastes good and is served quickly what more could you need

Amazing burgers, wonderful pies! I would recommend to order for takeout, because they don't have much space to eat inside in winter. In summer you can enjoy your food outside - they set up tables in their fenced yard.

Tommy's is a small place, but does steady business. Burgers are tasty, would have preferred medium rare. Onion rings, a bit on the bland side. Shakes are okay, on the small side for the price. Limited seating, but overall not a bad place for lunch.

I'll always keep coming back for the best Philly in Anchorage! Been coming here since the original owner Ron was making them 18 years ago and it was a pleasure meeting Tommy! He has kept the best of the old and made it become a must stop place when ever I can get to Anchorage! It's worth the wait and you are not going to be disappointed.
The best burgers in town. Absolutely. The service isn't fancy but they are always nice and know what they're doing. Especially fun in summer on their deck

Great food but prices are about $1.50 too high. $8 for a cheeseburger is excessive. Fries are delicious though, and $2 for a small and $4 for a large is a bit high, but the portions are a good size. I do think the large should be $3.50, so you feel like you're getting a deal. 

Service was good, staff is very friendly and nice.

The dining area is huge.  I went to dinner around six in the evening, on a high school prom night that I wasn't aware of, and was told that there would be around s 45 minute wait.  I was seated in less than 15.  I ordered the blackened halibut with garlic mashed potatoes and broccoli.  The food was deliscious though the portions were rather small.  Not so with the dessert.  I had their famous bread pudding and it was really good.  Prices range from around $12-$40.  I had an ice tea with my meal and it came to a little over $50.  All in all, a very nice dining experience and I would definitely go there again.

Suprisingly it was a good experience the wait to get items was a little bit longer than anticipated but overall the food was delicious. The Anchorage nachos are a must try and would recommend. I did like the halibut and the coconut and raspberry beer. Was not a fan of the jalapeno cornbread the syrup makes it taste burnt in the cast iron skillet, maybe because it was cooked way to long. Had a bite of the shrimp and grits a little spicy packed with a lot of heat was a little much on the heat side but was good.But for a place that seems like there is not a lot of good eating this would be one place I would stop again when I come back to when I fly through. Folks here are pretty nice.

Top-notch all around. Had a flight of 5 beers, all of which were excellent. Ordered the ahi, and it was superb. Even if it hadn't been seared, it was sushi grade and delectable. The best parts were the service and the people. A former employee was sitting at the bar, and every person working there who walked by greeted him with a smile or a hug. That says a lot about this place. When in Anchorage, don't miss it!

The staff were very prompt and polite.  Felt like I had come here often although it was our first time.  The food was fantastic, by far 5 stars on up!  Also these guys helped me impress my wife by getting us seats at the fireplace.  If I could give more stars I would.  Hats off guys.

One of the best casual restaurants in Anchorage. The service is always fantastic, the food is very good. They have a full bar and local brews. I have a favorite dish, jambalaya fettuccine, my wife tries different dishes and has never had a bad one.
Fabulous evening for my 50th.  Beautifully set up,  food was exactly what we asked for.  Bar staff and security were fabulous too
They took my korkscrewer away because it's a weapon, but i work as a Waiter, and new in GB, but 0 understanding... After all nice party!

The service was terrible. Was stood at bar for about 10 minutes before somebody acknowledged me and offered to serve me. I wouldn't mind but it was not busy at all. 

Staff seemed more interested in playing with their mobile phones as opposed to doing there jobs.
One of a few plate opening places.  Good mix of music

I didn't go to solstice for a long time. But probably this will be my last time. Because when I come in I paid for the entry what was fine for me. But security guard told me I need to leave my coat at the entrance because I cant be inside wearing it, while other people was inside with coats they just told me thats the policy. I only came for few bears in the garden. Im feeling cold, as I'm just with t-shirt this policy is very bad for customer experience as i will probably get cold.

So, this place lives up to the hype.. and fully agree with the 5 stars. Salmon cakes, mushroom omelets were outstanding- the kitchen knows what they are doing. Coffee is excellent. Prices are very reasonable for the quality of food. Make reservations or get here early. Service is excellent.

First, and foremost, make an online reservation. Otherwise, you will wait for an undetermined time. Even a resident didn't know you could make reservations. He and his family have always shown up and waited. Street parking is limited. There is a lot across the street that requires a credit/debit card to park. It was $6 for the 1st hour. Now about the food. It was very good, and you won't go home hungry. Their pancakes are larger than the plate. There is a great selection of foods. Note: They are only open for breakfast and lunch. Plan accordingly. And I recommend starting with a homemade cinnamon roll with their cream cheese icing. Consider sharing or save for later. Btw, I am not a coffee drinker (don't judge). They have a coffee and espresso bar with some baked goods for there or to go.

THE spot to go for brunch in Anchorage, although I probably shouldn't post that as the lines can already be pretty long.  That said, they have waiting buzzer things now, so it's not as bad to hang around for your table.  The omelettes and soups and salads are phenomenal.  They have a hot sauce bar too, which ... is just nice to have.  Staff are always friendly and the vibe is comfortable at any time of year!  Very kid-friendly too.
Good food and a busy brunch crowd made this a fun place to have some tasty eats. Portions were large and food was comfort style. An Anchorage institution.

Great place with great staff. It can be busy, best time is always early in the work week. Parking can be rough and dont forget to pay as I was warned the parking meters are well watched. Food is amazing, great Eggs Benedict with many options.

Amazing dinner last night 5 floors above our room! The view is gorgeous 😍😍 The staff is amazing and friendly. Boy oh boy it was the BEST food I have EVER had at a restaurant. The pork chop literally melted in my mouth and the brussel sprout leaves that came with was to die for! Highly highly recommend this place for special occasions!!!

Very fancy food. You definitely get what you pay for. I would recommend going when the sun is up or you will end up looking into the dark void that is Alaskan nights. Servers are on top of their game.

The service was wonderful, Ryan. The wine was very good. Love the setting and the scenery. The salmon was a too fresh. It was raw in the middle. Disappointed in the salmon. The squash soup was good. Very expensive.
Unbelievable experience, unlike any other! Incredible views and food. Pocketbook will be lighter after going here (we had four people in our group) but one of the best meals possible in Alaska!!!

I visit every month with my friends from the now defunct Rotary Club of Tring. My personal experience is therefore only relevant to Wednesday lunch times. The service on Wednesdays is very good, with two very friendly and helpful waitresses. The food is good value and would never claim to be Cordon Bleu. It is a good example of a pub serving traditional British food. Inexpensive and simple.

I’m not sure how this place isn’t rated higher. We were impressed by the food we had. We took advantage of the Happy Hour small plate and appetizer specials before having dinner at 5:00. Everything we ordered was devoured. The service was great too. We highly recommend the black cod. Goodness! It was SO good! We split it, so the picture below is just a half order of the black cod entree.

Orso is an outstanding place to have dinner. The wooden decor is on the high-end side. The staff is professional and quick to our needs. I ordered the seafood mac & cheese and the seafood chowder; both are super rich & delicious. They also have an excellent selection of drinks. I highly recommend this place.

Celebrating a birthday! Great food & drinks. Hubby got the lamb sank, AMAZING! I had the ribeye, YUM!. A couple bottles of wine. Desserts were incredible. Tiramisu & bread pudding. We will definitely be going back!

The service was excellent. The atmosphere isn't really conducive to a quiet conversation, but I also went after work. I was disappointed with the food and the drinks, especially considering the cost. My appetizer was smothered with parmesan and there was little flavor to my cocktail. My date ordered the lamb shank and enjoyed it, as well as 2/3 of his whiskey flight. The dessert was yummy, but not particularly special. I would go again, but order from the seafood menu.

Really liked the atmosphere here.  I enjoyed my hot food the whole meal.  I was also very impressed when I saw a bus-person let a senior hold his arm.  He walked her to her table very patiently like he walking his own Grammy.  A place you wouldn't be embarrassed to take a first date to.

Had a romantic dinner with my husband here for my birthday. Beautiful restaurant, wonderful staff, delicious food and drinks. Waitress (can’t recall her name, I think it was Jeannine) was knowledgeable, funny, and personal. My husband had the special, it was halibut, which was tasty but very small portioning. My plate had large portions so I guess it depends on what you order. Overall the experience was great!

My friend and I love discovering new places especially when we travel. I found this online before we went to Rome and booked for dinner. We ended up having breakfast twice and lunch twice.. If you love your açai bowls or your smoothies in the morning, this is perfect, if you love pancakes, then this is for you too, of course the menu has more to offer. Here’s just a selection of what we tried. Everyone needs to try this place. Delicious
One of my favorite small downtown restaurants.  Great lunch and dinner.  Unique and flavorful dishes.  Great service and atmosphere.  Parking can be tricky during busy times.

The bartenders here make some rad drinks for sure! I’m not a mixed drink kind of person but that’s all I order at this restaurant. They put on a show and give you some attitude....in a good way! The beef curry is the best I’ve ever had.....Great restaurant!
the service and drinks were exceptional.  but I didnt really like what I ordered. next time I'll get something else. but the dragon drink is amazing!!!
